e against existing documentation\\n4. Edit only the sections that are actually out of date\\n5. Re-read each file after editing to confirm it is valid\\n\\n## Rules\\n- If no documentation changes are needed, report success immediately\\n- Only report fail if an actual write to a doc file failed\\n- Do not invent behavior not present in source code\\n- If the drift is large, update only sections affected by the current change rather than reconciling everything\\n- Spend no more than a few minutes on comparison'_\n    82→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    83→\n    84→- **[lesson-20260306-008]** (new_step, confidence: high) Four steps remain orphaned in the workflow: check-vet-build-steps, check-vet-build-wiring, check-preflight, and check-orphaned-steps. They have step definitions and edges from their own results but no incoming edges from other steps, so they never execute. These were added by previous evolution cycles but never wired into the main flow.\n    85→  _Action: Wire check-vet-build-steps between test:success and update-docs: change 'test:success -> update-docs' to 'test:success -> check-vet-build-steps', add 'check-vet-build-steps:success -> update-docs' and 'check-vet-build-steps:fail -> fix'. Remove check-vet-build-wiring, check-preflight, and check-orphaned-steps as they are redundant meta-validation steps that should not be part of the production workflow — their concerns should be addressed by the evolution process itself, not by in-workflow script steps._\n    86→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    87→\n    88→- **[lesson-20260306-007]** (new_step, confidence: high) 27 out of 28 total runs with zero step results recorded (adding 10 new: develop-firm-lark, develop-vivid-brook, develop-quiet-vale, develop-warm-hare, develop-bold-elm, develop-bright-hawk, develop-deft-elm, develop-light-cove, develop-cool-vale, develop-proud-reef). Every run continues to fail before executing any step. This is now overwhelmingly the dominant failure mode — no workflow-level improvement can have any effect until containers can actually start and execute steps.\n    89→  _Action: This is no longer a workflow evolution issue. The container runtime or daemon is fundamentally broken. Before any further workflow changes: (1) Check daemon logs for startup errors, (2) Verify Docker is running and accessible, (3) Test container creation manually. The preflight step suggestion from prior cycles would help diagnose this IF steps could execute at all, but they cannot. The root cause is infrastructure-level, not workflow-level._\n    90→  _Evidence: develop-firm-lark, develop-vivid-brook, develop-quiet-vale, develop-warm-hare, develop-bold-elm, develop-bright-hawk, develop-deft-elm, develop-light-cove, develop-cool-vale, develop-proud-reef, develop-calm-vine, develop-grand-reef, develop-calm-crane, develop-quiet-tide, develop-glad-vine, develop-proud-glen, develop-glad-bear, develop-firm-glen, develop-vivid-oak, develop-brave-vale, develop-swift-wolf, develop-vivid-lake, develop-glad-reef, develop-swift-pine, develop-keen-dale, develop-grand-oak, develop-glad-vale_\n    91→\n    92→- **[lesson-20260306-005]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The fix.md prompt is still corrupted — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual fix instructions. This has persisted for 5+ evolution cycles without being corrected, likely because the evolution agent lacks write permission to the file.\n    93→  _Action: Replace the entire contents of fix.md with the intended prompt: a header instructing the agent to fix validation failures, a placeholder for validation output injection, and learned rules (analyze root cause before editing, run failing tests in isolation, make minimal targeted changes, try different approach if previous fix visible, run the exact failing test command and confirm it passes before reporting success)._\n    94→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    95→\n    96→- **[lesson-20260306-006]*